AB  - The purpose of this study was to describe the evaluation of the first clinical experience of male nursing students. Method: A convenience sample was selected from nine students for first clinical experience on medical ward, surgical ward, orthopedic ward, Rehabilitation ward, Operating room, recovery room, and nursing home. Ages of the students were between 20-29 years old. Individual interviews were utilized. Participants agreed to participate in the study and signed the consent form. The research data was collected from March 26th to May 6th when the materials were saturated. Results: 1) Subjects increased self-confidence during their first clinical experience. 2) Subjects satisfied role of the nursing practice. 3) Subjects had adjustment skills after first clinical practice. 4) Subjects felt poor coordination between theory and practice after their first clinical practice. 5) Subjects were getting along with friends. 6) Subjects felt overwhelmed due to hard study and clinical practice at the hospital after their first clinical experience and they were very irritable before they go to the hospital. Conclusion: Male nursing students have a positive attitude about clinical practice at the hospital and negative attitude about 1 st clinical practice. It is necessary to provide support system and guidance about clinical practice before the first clinical practice. It is nessecery to revise curriculum to satisfy the male student needs and it is nessecery to develop protocol and meetings with male students. It is nessecery to have evaluation meetings with students, clinical instructors and the head nurse on the ward. These days, many man choose a nurse as their job because they want to care various people and it guarantee professionalism, stability and power. However, social identity about man nurse lacks and it's difficult for man nurse to adapt the hospital. Therefore, barrier of the education of nursing man students need to be broken and the social bases for them growing as a professional in the equal environment like women's need. Also, it's required to develop a program or a curriculum which help them to carry out their role. © 2017 International Information Institute.
