tation of the positive attitude are determined. The constituents of the technological component can be considered as pedagogical conditions for the realization of a reflexive orientation in the formation of a positive attitude toward learning of trade by future marketers. The significance of the study is to clarify the role and features of the positive attitude of students to learning of a marketer's trade; in revealing the content of the reflexive orientation in the formation of a positive attitude toward a marketer's trade learning, in developing technological aspects of forming students' positive attitude to a marketer's trade learning that can be realized in the process of professional training of students of other specialties.
